              <h3>Caleb</h3>
              <p>Creating and sharing nutrient-dense, neo-traditional, and (usually) delicious meals with friends, family, and my community is a deep passion of mine. Much aligned with my musical tastes, I love to cook with complex and aggressive flavor profiles from all corners of the globe. I assert that every dish should include a healthy pinch of cayenne, love, and perhaps a few dashes of homemade hot sauce. I love to explore and experience rich flavors and aromas, whether that’s coming from home-cooked feasts or a decadent craft beer or cocktail.</p>
              <p>Studying and incorporating regenerative agriculture and organic gardening into my life has been richly rewarding and I don’t see myself turning back. As a professional ecologist and arborist, I also dabble in edible/medicinal plant and mushroom foraging. I don’t care for politics, but I do strongly believe that supporting local, values-based businesses is the only solution to shifting our globalized, profit-driven economy into something that truly supports both our planet and our people. And that change must happen from the ground up, with like-minded folks taking action (i.e. voting with you wallet) to support whatever causes resonate with you. For me, that cause is sticking it to The Man and overhauling how we (i.e. humanity) feed ourselves...with no compromises on deliciousness! Essentially, I’m a huge nerd and animal lover, and I strive to walk the walk when it comes to compassionate, healthy, and sustainable living \m/</p>
